service_url = 'https://babelnet.io/v6/getSynsetIds'

lemma = 'passive safety'
lang = 'EN'
key  = '4d425ff2-1193-4714-abf1-70e2b21ee9f3'

params = {
        'lemma' : lemma,
        'searchLang' : lang,
        'key'  : key
}

url = service_url + '?' + urllib.parse.urlencode(params)
print(url)
request = urllib.request.Request(url)
request.add_header('Accept-encoding', 'gzip')
response = urllib.request.urlopen(request)

if response.info().get('Content-Encoding') == 'gzip':
        buf = BytesIO( response.read())
        f = gzip.GzipFile(fileobj=buf)
        data = json.loads(f.read())
        for result in data:
                print(result['id'])

Retrieve the information of a given synset¶

In [3]:
service_url = 'https://babelnet.io/v6/getSynset'

id = 'bn:17089601n'
key  = '4d425ff2-1193-4714-abf1-70e2b21ee9f3'

params = {
    'id' : id,
    'key'  : key
}

url = service_url + '?' + urllib.parse.urlencode(params)
print(url)
request = urllib.request.Request(url)
request.add_header('Accept-encoding', 'gzip')
response = urllib.request.urlopen(request)

if response.info().get('Content-Encoding') == 'gzip':
    buf = BytesIO( response.read())
    f = gzip.GzipFile(fileobj=buf)
    data = json.loads(f.read())

    # retrieving BabelSense data
    senses = data['senses']
    for result in senses:
        id_ = result.get('properties')['synsetID']['id']    
        lemma = result.get('properties')['lemma']['lemma']
        language = result.get('properties')['language']
        print(id_, language,lemma)        
    print('\n')
    
    # retrieving BabelGloss data
    glosses = data['glosses']
    for result in glosses:
        gloss = result.get('gloss')
        language = result.get('language')
        print(gloss, language)
    print('\n')
    
    # retrieving BabelImage data
    images = data['images']    
    for result in images:
        url = result.get('url')
        language = result.get('language')
        name = result.get('name')        
        try:
            print(name)
            picture = plt.imread(url, format='jpeg')
            plt.imshow(picture)
            plt.show()
        except:
            pass

Retrieve the senses of a given word¶

In [4]:
service_url = 'https://babelnet.io/v6/getSenses'

lemma = 'passive safety'
lang = 'EN'
key  = '4d425ff2-1193-4714-abf1-70e2b21ee9f3'

params = {
    'lemma' : lemma,
    'searchLang' : lang,
    'key'  : key
}

url = service_url + '?' + urllib.parse.urlencode(params)
print(url)
request = urllib.request.Request(url)
request.add_header('Accept-encoding', 'gzip')
response = urllib.request.urlopen(request)

if response.info().get('Content-Encoding') == 'gzip':
    buf = BytesIO( response.read())
    f = gzip.GzipFile(fileobj=buf)
    data = json.loads(f.read())

    # retrieving BabelSense data
    for result in data:
        
        lemma = result.get('properties')['lemma']['lemma']
        language = result.get('properties')['language']
        source = result.get('properties')['source']
#         print(result)
        print(lemma, language, source)

Retrieve a list of BabelNet IDs given a resource identifier¶

In [5]:
service_url = 'https://babelnet.io/v6/getSynsetIdsFromResourceID'

id      = 'Passive_safety'
lang    = 'EN'
pos     = 'NOUN'
source  = 'WIKI'
key 	= '4d425ff2-1193-4714-abf1-70e2b21ee9f3'

params = {
        'id'     : id,
        'searchLang'   : lang,
        'pos'    : pos,
        'source' : source,
        'key'    : key
}

url = service_url + '?' + urllib.parse.urlencode(params)
print(url)
request = urllib.request.Request(url)
request.add_header('Accept-encoding', 'gzip')
response = urllib.request.urlopen(request)

if response.info().get('Content-Encoding') == 'gzip':
    buf = BytesIO( response.read())
    f = gzip.GzipFile(fileobj=buf)
    data = json.loads(f.read())
    for result in data:
        print(result['id'])

Retrieve edges of a given BabelNet synset¶

In [9]:
service_url = 'https://babelnet.io/v6/getOutgoingEdges'

id = 'bn:17089601n'
key  = '4d425ff2-1193-4714-abf1-70e2b21ee9f3'

params = {
    'id' : id,
    'key'  : key
}

url = service_url + '?' + urllib.parse.urlencode(params)
print(url)
request = urllib.request.Request(url)
request.add_header('Accept-encoding', 'gzip')
response = urllib.request.urlopen(request)

if response.info().get('Content-Encoding') == 'gzip':
    buf = BytesIO( response.read())
    f = gzip.GzipFile(fileobj=buf)
    data = json.loads(f.read())

    # retrieving Edges data
    for result in data:
        target = result.get('target')
        language = result.get('language')

        # retrieving BabelPointer data
        pointer = result['pointer']
        relation = pointer.get('name')
        group = pointer.get('relationGroup')
        print(target, language, pointer, relation, group)

Retrieve hypernyms, hyponyms and antonyms of a given BabelNet synset¶

In [7]:
service_url = 'https://babelnet.io/v6/getOutgoingEdges'

id = 'bn:17089601n'
key  = '4d425ff2-1193-4714-abf1-70e2b21ee9f3'

params = {
    'id' : id,
    'key'  : key
}

url = service_url + '?' + urllib.parse.urlencode(params)
print(url)
request = urllib.request.Request(url)
request.add_header('Accept-encoding', 'gzip')
response = urllib.request.urlopen(request)

if response.info().get('Content-Encoding') == 'gzip':
    buf = BytesIO( response.read())
    f = gzip.GzipFile(fileobj=buf)
    data = json.loads(f.read())

    # retrieving Edges data
    for result in data:
        target = result.get('target')
        language = result.get('language')

        # retrieving BabelPointer data
        pointer = result['pointer']
        relation = pointer.get('name')
        group = pointer.get('relationGroup')

        # Types of relationGroup: HYPERNYM,  HYPONYM, MERONYM, HOLONYM, OTHER
        if ('hypernym' in group.lower() or 'hyponym' in group.lower()):
                print (str(language) + "\t" + str(target) + "\t" + str(relation) + "\t" + str(group))
        elif ('antonym' in relation.lower()):
                print (str(language) + "\t" + str(target) + "\t" + str(relation) + "\t" + str(group))
